A student-centered digital management platform tailored for Vietnamese university students to balance study, time, finances, and well-being.

User Review Required
IMPORTANT

Directory Structure Review: Please review the proposed directory structure below to ensure it covers all student needs (Study, Time, Tasks, Budget, Well-being) before I start the implementation.

Proposed Directory Structure
unilife-vn-dashboard/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx              # Root layout (Mobile-first, Dark mode ready)
│   ├── page.tsx                # Landing / Dashboard Overview
│   ├── study-planner/
│   │   └── page.tsx            # Credit-based course & exam manager
│   ├── time-management/
│   │   └── page.tsx            # Schedules & Balance tracking
│   ├── tasks-habits/
│   │   └── page.tsx            # Daily tasks & Habit streaks
│   ├── student-budget/
│   │   └── page.tsx            # Allowance, Rent, Food tracking
│   └── well-being/
│       └── page.tsx            # Stress levels & Self-care tracking
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                     # shadcn/ui primitives
│   ├── dashboard/
│   │   ├── progress-overview.tsx  # Completion rates, streaks
│   │   ├── outcome-projection.tsx # Dynamic projections (GPA, Savings)
│   │   ├── priority-controls.tsx  # Sliders for generic inputs
│   │   └── student-insights.tsx   # Context-aware alerts (Workload warnings)
│   └── layout/
│       ├── mobile-nav.tsx      # Bottom nav for mobile usage
│       └── sidebar.tsx         # Desktop sidebar
├── lib/
│   ├── calculations.ts         # Logic for GPA, Budget Remainder, Time Checks
│   ├── constants.ts            # Config (e.g., VN University grading scales)
│   └── types.ts                # TypeScript interfaces
├── __tests__/
│   ├── study-logic.test.ts     # Workload calculation tests
│   └── budget-logic.test.ts    # Expense projection tests
└── public/
Proposed Changes
Tech Stack
Framework: Next.js 14 (App Router)
Styling: Tailwind CSS (Calm, productivity-focused palette)
UI Library: shadcn/ui
Testing: Jest
core Components
[NEW] 
progress-overview.tsx
Visualizes "Student Progress" (e.g., % of credits finished, budget used).
[NEW] 
outcome-projection.tsx
Real-time updates based on user inputs (e.g., "If I spend 2M VND more, I will be broke by day 20").
[NEW] 
student-insights.tsx
Smart alerts: "Warning: Exam period approaching, reduce part-time work hours."
Logic & Testing
[NEW] 
calculations.ts
calculateStudyLoad(credits, weeks)
projectBudget(allowance, fixedExpenses, dailySpend)
assessBalance(studyHours, workHours, restHours)
[NEW] 
tests
Unit tests to verify the above logic ensures strict confidence in projections.
Verification Plan
Automated Tests
npm test to run Jest suites for logic.
Manual Verification
Mobile Responsiveness: Critical for students on the go.
Dark Mode: Check visibility for late-night sessions.
Interactivity: Verify sliders update projections instantly using React state.
